Online's stock. By Saul Hansell.
</P>
<P>
   Y2K-BUG-AD-COLUMN (London) _ ``Get Your Business Ready for the
Bug,'' scream 3,175 billboards in and around London as part of an
ambitious $17 million advertising campaign that seeks to make small
and midsized businesses aware of the technological apocalypse that
is scheduled to wreak havoc on computers at the end of the century
if they have not been upgraded to understand when the year changes
from 1999 to 2000. By Andrew Ross Sorkin.
</P>
<P>
   PATENTS (Undated) _ Patents for getting more promotional time
from TV; using TV sets to track people and pets; live TV in
