for women who might like the odds. By Lisa Napoli.
</P>
<P>
   CULTURE
</P>
<P>
   (Moved in `e' category)
</P>
<P>
   WWII-RUSSIA-MUSEUM- (Washington) _ One of Hitler's uniforms and
the Soviet flag that flew over the Reichstag after the fall of
Berlin are among some 500 World War II artifacts on display for the
first time in the United States in a new exhibition at the Ronald
Reagan Center for International Trade. ``World War II Through
Russian Eyes'' includes photographs, documentary film footage,
battlefield maps and personal mementos of those Russians who fought
and died during the war. The exhibition, which is free, is the
result of a collaboration between Kermit Weeks, president of the
Historical Artifacts Museum near Orlando, Fla., and Col. Alexander
Nikonov, director of Moscow's Central Armed Forces Museum. By
Melissa McNamara.
