<P>
   NETHAWAY-COLUMN _ If Starr's final report to Congress includes
credible evidence that Clinton willfully broke the law, surely
Clinton's approval ratings will drop. If not, America's rule of law
is in jeopardy. (Nethaway, Waco Tribune-Herald) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   SCHUETT-COLUMN _ GIBSONBURG, Ohio _ Teachers don't ask for a
whole lot _ a little respect, some new textbooks from time to time,
and once in a while, a raise would be nice. Most of us aren't
militant and know little of the function of much maligned teacher's
unions. But you know what we'd like most of all? We'd like for
ambitious politicians to stop using teachers and education as
political footballs. (Schuett, Atlanta Journal-Constitution.)
MOVED.
