the mortgage will get paid off and deceased parents will leave
behind an inheritance. That patrimony may be considerable:
Economists estimate $12 trillion is now in the hands of the fading
World War II generation whose heirs are the 76 million Americans
born between 1946 and 1964. (Geewax, Atlanta Journal-Constitution.)
MOVED. (f, k)
