most people need them to be. Unless you're into the latest and
greatest 3D computer games, you probably don't need a
top-of-the-line machine. Even former President Bush is taking
advantage of a cycle in PC technology in which low-cost hardware is
more than adequate for most computing tasks. By DWIGHT SILVERMAN.
</P>
