colony called Yaddo. In the same densely wooded Saratoga landscape
where Edgar Allan Poe roamed 150 years ago, the secluded 400-acre
Yaddo estate is a sprawling terrain of blue stucco barns and
tranquil ponds, blossoming gardens, a pair of spooky graveyards and
a grand 55-room Victorian mansion. By THOMAS CHRISTIAN.
</P>
