<HEADLINE>
.
</HEADLINE>
  
(For use by NYTimes News Service clients) The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following stories
today for use by NYTimes News Service clients. They will move in
the ``e'' entertainment news file. For questions, contact Jimmy
Johnson at the Daily News, (818) 713-3695. 
. 
SHANNEN-TV (Los Angeles) _ Shannen Doherty and Aaron Spelling are
back together again. After a very public Hollywood falling out that
led to her departure from ``Beverly Hills 90210,'' the two have
mended fences and she of temperamental reputation is back on the
air in another Spelling project. The show, which is set to air on
the WB this fall, is called ``Charmed,'' a drama in which Shannen
plays a witch. By Keith Marder. 
. 
FENCING_MOVIES (Los Angeles) _ As a child, Pat Cherry stared up at
the big screen, watching reverently, his heroes saving beautiful
damsels and slaying villains with the slice of a sword. Zorro. The
Three Musketeers. Cyrano de Bergerac. Those images of chivalrous
men finally led Cherry to emulate their art through fencing. By
Jenifer Hanrahan. 
. 

