<HEADLINE>
&HT;    
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Cast-favorite `Avengers' making a move
 &HT;    By Russ DeVault
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Soundtracks continue to figure heavilly on the pop chart, with
``Armageddon'' at No. 2, ``City of Angels'' at No. 5 and ``Dr.
Dolittle'' at No. 7, while ``Hope Floats'' has been No. 1 on the
country list for nine weeks. Now comes Atlantic's ``The Avengers,''
which has a musical cast certain to produce hot sales and chart
numbers.
</P>
<P>
   The 12 tracks include new material from Sinead O'Connor, Grace
Jones, Annie Lennox and PJ Harvey with other cuts by Stereo MCs,
Roni Size, the Verve Pipe and Dishwalla.
</P>
<P>
   -- Alpha Blondy &AMP; the Solar System, ``Yitzhak Rabin'' (Tuff
Gong). First American tour in six years ongoing.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Dance With Me'' soundtrack (Epic). Includes cuts by Gloria
Estefan, Vanessa Williams and Ruben Blades.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``How Stella Got Her Groove Back'' soundtrack (Flyte Tyme).
Jazzie B, Stevie Wonder &AMP; Wyclef Jean among contributors.
</P>
<P>
   -- Dolly Parton, ``Hungry Again'' (Decca). Four-time Grammy
winner returns to country, folk and gospel roots. Due Aug. 25.
</P>
<P>
   -- Snoop Dogg, ``Da Game Is To Be Sold, Not To Be Told'' (No
Limit). Review in Thursday Living. Grade: C+.
</P>
<P>
   -- Gillian Welch, ``Hell Among the Yearlings'' (Almo Sounds).
Review in Thursday Living. Grade: B.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
