<P>
   VINEYARD _ EDGARTOWN, Mass. _ When the Clintons come to Martha's
Vineyard next week, some local folks will pack up and leave their
beloved island until the First Family finishes its vacation. It's
not that they dislike President Clinton or even that they dread the
congestion and commotion that have accompanied him on three
previous late summer stays. But housing is scarce during August,
the seasonal peak, so some residents now rent their home to the
legions of Secret Service agents, White House staffers and
journalists who descend on the picturesque isle seven miles off
Cape Cod. And why not, since some beachfront properties can rent
for up to $80,000 for the month of August? (Dart, Cox News
Service). EDS: Moving in (l) Lifestyle and (w) Washington
categories.
</P>
<P>
   VINEYARD-SCANDAL _ OAK BLUFFS, Mass. _ This harbor town was
founded on notions of sin and redemption, so it is not surprising
that Washington's scandalous goings-on are a hot topic of
conversation as Martha's Vineyard prepares for President Clinton's
vacation. (Dart, Cox News Service)
</P>
<P>
   VINEYARD-BOX _ Facts about Martha's Vineyard (locations,
population, average temperature in August, etc.). (Cox News
Service)
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
