<HEADLINE>
WHERE ARE THEY NOW? 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By DAVE WALKER  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   BEVERLY HILLS - In retrospect, ``American Graffiti'' was a magic
moment; a bunch of young unknowns came together and made something
much bigger than themselves. Take a look at the family tree:
</P>
<P>
   It was only the second film for George Lucas, who later made the
``Star ``Wars'' trilogy and collaborated with Steven Spielberg on
the Indiana Jones'' film series. He's now working on the f irst of
a series of ``Star Wars'' prequels, which is expected to be
released next year.
</P>
<P>
   Candy Clark won an Academy Award nomination for playing Debbie,
Terry the Toad's dream girl. She later had roles in ``The Blob,''
``The Man Who Fell to Earth,'' ``Blue Thunder'' and ``Radioland
Murders.''
</P>
<P>
   Richard Dreyfuss moved on from Curt to ``The Apprenticeship of
Duddy Kravitz,'' ``Jaws,'' ``The Goodbye Girl,'' ``Close Encounters
of the Third Kind'' and ``Down and Out in Beverly Hills,' ' among
others.
</P>
<P>
   After Bob Falfa, Harrison Ford appeared in ``The Conversation,''
the ``Star ``Wars'' trilogy, the ``Indiana Jones'' movies, ``Blade
Runner,'' ``Working Girl,'' ``Air Force One'' and ``Six Days, Seven
Nights,'' among others.
</P>
<P>
   Bo Hopkins was Joe, leader of the Pharaohs, and has since
appeared in ``The Getaway,'' ``The Man Who Loved Cat Dancing,''
``Midnight Express'' and ``U-Turn.''
</P>
<P>
   Before ``American Graffiti,'' Ron Howard starred in TV's ``The
Andy
</P>
<P>
   Griffith Show'' and the film ``The Music Man.'' After ``American
Graffiti,'' he starred in the ABC sitcom ``Happy Days'' and the
film ``The Shootist.'' As a director, he made ``Night Shift,''
``Splash,'' ``Cocoon,'' ``Backdraft,'' ``Apollo 13'' and
``Ransom,'' among others.
</P>
<P>
   After his role as John, Paul Le Mat made his mark as Melvin
Dummar in ``Melvin and Howard.'' He also stars in the upcoming
films ``The Outfitters'' and ``American History X.''
</P>
<P>
   After playing Carol, Mackenzie Phillips starred as Julie Cooper
in the TV series ``One Day at a Time,'' and toured with her dad's
pop group, The Mamas and the Papas. Recently, she has appeared in
the musical ``Grease.''
</P>
<P>
   Kathleen Quinlan made her debut as Peg in ``American Graffiti,''
and has since starred in ``The Doors,'' ``Apollo 13,''
``Breakdown'' and ``My Giant.''
</P>
<P>
   After Terry the Toad, Charles Martin Smith worked in
``Starman,'' ``The Buddy Holly Story'' and the ``Untouchables.'' In
1983 he co-wrote and starred in ``Never Cry Wolf.'' More recently,
he directed the premiere episode of the TV series ``Buffy, the
Vampire Slayer.''
</P>
<P>
   After her big break as Curt's Teen Angel, Suzanne Somers starred
on the ABC sitcom ``Three's Company,'' then in countless
made-for-TV movies, attempted TV series and fitness infomercials.
She now co-hosts the CBS series ``Candid Camera.''
</P>
<P>
   Cindy Williams was Laurie, then Shirley in the hit ABC sitcom
``Laverneand Shirley.'' She also starred in the Francis Ford
Coppola film ``The Conversation,'' and appeared in the films ``Fat
her of the Bride I and II'' and ``Meet Wally Sparks.'' &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
