<HEADLINE>
IT'LL SOON BE TIME TO PARTY LIKE IT'S 1962 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By DAVE WALKER  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   BEVERLY HILLS - A DVD Collector's Edition of ``American
Graffiti,'' scheduled for a Sept. 15 release, will include a
two-hour making-of documentary and will retail for $34.98.
</P>
<P>
   The 25th anniversary video re-release of the film, also
scheduled for Sept. 15, will include 10 minutes of the making-of
documentary, will retail for $19.98 and will be available in both
pan-and-scan and letterbox versions. A version subtitled in Spanish
will cost $14.98.
</P>
<P>
   Also in September, ``American Graffiti'' will be inducted into
the Cruisin' Hall of Fame. Ceremonies will be held Sept. 17-30 at
the 1998 Statler Bros. Route 66 Rendezvous in San Bernardino,
Calif., and organizers of the event are conducting a nationwide
search to locate some of the cars used in the film.
</P>
<P>
   So anyone with information on the whereabouts of the yellow
deuce coupe driven by Paul LeMat's character, the 1955 Chevy driven
by Harrison Ford's character or the 1956 Thunderbird driven by
Suzanne Somers' character (or any of the other featured vehicles)
should call the San Bernardino Convention and Visitors Bureau at
909-889-3980.  &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
