<HEADER>
A6864 &Cx1f; tth-z
u v &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BUDGET-SPOT-SPI &LR;      08-10 0377
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BUDGET-SPOT-SPI </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Seattle Post-Intelligencer pnans to move the following
stories for clients of the NYTimes News Service for editions of
Tuesday, Aug. 11, and thereafter. If you have any questions, please
call Tina May at (206) 448-8355.
</P>
<P>
   BOEING-SEALAUNCH (Undated) A state dept. official confirms that
it has suspended Boeing's Sea Launch venture, which was to have
launched the first rocket from the ocean later this year.
Washington Post first reported the suspension came because
sensitive technology was exchanged with the Russians. State
department official said the project can continue once Boeing
provides a new security framework, but this means no launch until
next year. A congressional source, who talked with state and
Boeing, says the case is very similar to that of Loral, which is
under investigation by Congress. In both cases, company executives
blew whistle on themselves. But in the Boeing case, apparently no
classified information was exchanged. Just technical.
</P>
<P>
   By James Wallace. (story will move in the ``f'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MICROSOFT-JUSTICE (Washington) Microsoft Monday asked a federal
judge to dismiss the lawsuit against it, arguing that neither the
facts nor the law are on the government's side. Motions refute many
of the main claims of the federal and state governments.
</P>
<P>
   By Michael Paulson. (story will move in the ``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   BBA-MARINERS (Toronto) Jose Cruz Jr. has been up, as a fan
favorite in Seattle, and down, sent to the minor leagues after
being traded to Toronto and encountering hitting problems. A look
at the controversial trade one year later, advancing the Mariners
series that starts Tuesday in Toronto.
</P>
<P>
   By Jim Street. (story will move in the ``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   FBN-COLUMN-VECSEY (Seattle) Conventional wisdom said the
Seahawks need Warren Moon. Let's forget conventional wisdom. Jon
Kitna looks like the real deal.
</P>
<P>
   By Laura Vecsey. (story will move in the ``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   FBN-SEAHAWKS (Cheney, Wash.) Seahawks at training camp.
</P>
<P>
   By Clare Farnsworth. (story will move in the ``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   GOLF-COLUMN-THIEL (Undated) On what separates a PGA club pro
from a touring pro.
</P>
<P>
   By Art Thiel. (story will move in the ``s'' category)
