   AFRICA-DEAD (Ramstein Air Base, Germany) _ The bodies of the
Americans killed in Nairobi are expected to arrive here Monday
evening: the scene at the arrival, Secretary of State Albright's
plans for returning with them to the United States, other details
on injured victims. By Craig R. Whitney. (Scheduled to move by 9
p.m.) 700-1,000 words.
</P>
<P>
   AFRICA-SURVIVE (Nairobi, Kenya) _ The harrowing story of Joanne
Grady-Huskey, whose husband, James, is a political officer at the
embassy in Nairobi. Taking her children to a doctor's appointment,
she parked two spots away from the truck believed to have carried
the explosives, and missed by only seconds being killed or badly
injured in the blast. By James C. McKinley Jr. (Story has moved.)
800 words.
</P>
<P>
   AFRICA-BOMBINGS (Nairobi, Kenya) _ As rescue teams dug through
the deep rubble of a collapsed building in a final, desperate
search for victims of the Kenya bombing, American investigating
teams began sorting the debris, in an equally painstaking search
for the tiniest clues. By Raymond Bonner. (Scheduled to move by 8
p.m.) 900 words.
</P>
