CENSUS (Undated) - Only the federal government could launch a war
that pits flush toilets against computers. But that's what's
happening as the Year 2000 Census fails to ask U.S. citizens
anything about computers or the Internet, spawing legilslation to
force the Census Bureau to revamp the questions. By DAVID HOYE.
Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
FELICITY (Undated) - She is 22-year-old Keri Russell, star of WB
Network's most touted and envied new sitcom, ``Felicity,'' and she
has created more pre-season publicity buzz than even Calista
Flockhart's ``Ally McBeal'' did last year. What's it like to be the
center of such enormous attention, especially since her show hasn't
even aired yet? ``It's horrifying, to tell you the truth,'' she
said. ``I don't know how to deal with it. There definitely is more
pressure when everyone's expecting you to deliver.'' By JAIMEE
ROSE. Story moved in the ``E'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
MONTINI-COLUMN (Undated) - The message was recorded at 8:22 a.m.
Tuesday, Aug. 4. The caller, a woman, spoke for 30 seconds. ``Mr.
Montini,'' she says, ``my name is Debbie. I'm, I'm dying of liver
cancer and I just I wanted to tell you thank you very much for your
articles. Now that I have so little time I'm thanking all the
people that have done something special for me in my life...'' By
E.J.MONTINI. Story will move in the ``A'' and ``K'' categories. &QL; 
 &QL; 
GRAFFITI1 (Beverly Hills) _ Where were you in '72? The cast and
crew of ``American Graffiti`` were in northern California, shooting
a nostalgic little movie that would make history.
</P>
<P>
   The 1973 release _ its poster pitch line: ``Where were you in
'62?'' _ may be most notable as the project director George Lucas
did before ``Star Wars,`` but it got five Academy Award nominations
(including Best Picture), generated a superb soundtrack album,
introduced to the world a dazzling cast of young actors and may be
the most profitable movie ever made. This fall, a 25th anniversary
video and DVD release will offer fans an opportunity to revisit
Mel's Diner and its habitues. With GRAFFITI2, GRAFFITI3, GRAFFITI4.
By DAVE WALKER. Stories moved in the ``E'' category. &QL; 
