to sell a stand of ancient redwood trees to the federal and
California governments is close to unraveling. Budget negotiators
in Sacramento have dropped from the state's 1999 budget a $130
million appropriation needed to buy Houston-based Maxxam's
Headwaters Forest _ the largest stand of old-growth redwood trees
left in private hands. By DAVID IVANOVICH.
