</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-FALCONS-MILLER-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Louchiey's injury leaves plans on hold
 &HT;    By Matt Winkeljohn
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Corey Louchiey missed his fifth and sixth consecutive
practices with the Atlanta Falcons on Monday, but it's hard to tell
what's more sore _ his groin or the coaching staff that is aching
to evaluate him as a potential starter at right tackle.
</P>
<P>
   The Falcons gave Louchiey a two-year, $3.5 million contract to
replace Matt Willig, who left for Green Bay. But Louchiey, a
6-foot-8, 315-pound, three-year veteran, suffered a groin injury
near the end of the afternoon scrimmage in Jacksonville on Aug. 1
and hasn't practiced since.
</P>
<P>
   Nate Miller started in Friday's 31-16 preseason loss to
Tennessee, and rookie free agent Jose Portilla backed him up.
Neither player embarrassed himself, but the idea of either making a
first regular-season start on Sept. 6 against Kevin Greene and
Carolina is cause for pause.
</P>
<P>
   ``We needed (Louchiey) out here last week, but you can't do
anything about it,'' coach Dan Reeves said. ``As soon as he gets
healthy, he'll be in there because we need to evaluate him.''
</P>
<P>
   Louchiey, 26, rides an exercise bike outside the locker room and
strides around the practice fields. ``If you're hurt, you can't
play,'' he said. ``It's very, very, very frustrating, because I
need all the time I can get.''
</P>
<P>
   And Falcons quarterback Chris Chandler needs all the protection
he can get. Atlanta quarterbacks were sacked 54 times last year,
fifth-most in the league.
</P>
<P>
   ``Corey has to work. He knows that,'' offensive line coach Art
Shell said. ``We need to see him on the field.''
</P>
<P>
   Miller spent most of the 1995 and '96 seasons on the Falcons'
practice squad. He dressed for 12 games last year, playing little
in 11. His size (6-3, 310) and athletic ability are pluses, but his
technique needs work. He was involved in one of the two sacks
Atlanta surrendered Friday, when Oilers end Pratt Lyons got to Tony
Graziani.
</P>
<P>
   ``Pass protection is the thing (Miller) has got to work on,''
Shell said. ``The mental errors are tough on a young guy. His
footwork is fine. He has the athletic ability to play, but pass
protection is like dancing. You have to have good footwork and be
in step with everybody. It's choreographed.''
</P>
<P>
   Louchiey, a third-round draft choice of Buffalo in 1994, started
13 games the past three seasons with the Bills. Atlanta gave him a
$500,000 signing bonus and a base salary this season of $500,000.
</P>
<P>
   If he ends up proving as talented as the Falcons' scouting
report seems to indicate, he'll become a lot richer next year, when
his contract calls for an increase in salary to $1.5 million and a
$1 million bonus to make the team.
</P>
<P>
   NFL teams will start cutting players in two weeks, but Reeves
isn't counting on getting help that way.
</P>
<P>
   ``We'll do it probably with what we've got here,'' he said. ``I
don't think there's anything out there that's going to be better
than what we've got.''
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
