Charles Johnson. Johnson was the cornerstone of the Florida Marlins
franchise and a key player in their World Series title run last
year. Johnson has struggled some since being part of the Mike
Piazza trade, but he's still considered one of the game's emerging
stars at catcher.. &QL; 
By Howard Beck. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.)
