   &QL; 
FBC-RECRUIT (Long Beach, Calif.) _ His father is the most revered
football player in the history of the University of Mississippi.
And for the past four years his brother turned the University of
Tennessee into Peyton's Place. But chances are that Eli Manning, a
senior quarterback at Cardinal Isidore Newman High in New Orleans,
won't be spending his college days in Knoxville, Tenn., or Oxford,
Miss. &QL; 
By Long Beach Press-Telegram. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.)
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
BKO-BALTER (Los Angeles) _ Short appreciation of Sam Balter, the
ex-teacher, athlete, broadcaster and newspaper columnist who died
over the weekend at age 88. Balter talks of being a Jew on the U.S.
basketball team at the 1936 Olympics in Nazi Germany. &QL; 
By Joe Jares. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.)
</P>
