<HEADER>
A6978 &Cx1f; tad-z
u s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BBO-SERIES-TICKETS-CO     08-10 0378
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BBO-SERIES-TICKETS-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    World Series, playoff ticket prices increase
 &HT;    (EDS: To clarify that Major League Baseball has doubled ticket
prices, and prices will vary from city to city. Prices listed below
are for Atlanta.)
 &HT;    By I.J. Rosenberg
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Atlanta Braves season-ticket holders will get a
surprise in the mail this week, when the invoices for postseason
games arrive. Prices for World Series games have doubled to $150
per game for most seats.
</P>
<P>
   Tickets for the National League Championship Series games have
been increased by $10, although tickets for the Division Series
essentially will stay the same as last season.
</P>
<P>
   The prices for the National League Championship Series and World
Series were set by major league baseball during an executive
council meeting in June. The council is made up of team owners and
commissioner Bud Selig.
</P>
<P>
   ``Given the cost of tickets in other sports for their
championship events,'' Selig said Monday, ``our people felt that
the framework was there, that these were rational and fair prices.
There were people on the committee who were concerned, including
yours truly. But when we compared baseball to other sports,
everybody finally became very comfortable.''
</P>
<P>
   Asked if he felt fans would get upset at the increase, Selig
said, ``No. It's the World Series.''
</P>
<P>
   Although the Braves didn't make the Series last year, they
printed tickets _ $75 for box seats (dugout/suites, club, field and
terrace, field pavilion and terrace pavilion) and $50 for
upper-deck seats. This year, box seats will cost $150 and
upper-deck seats $100.
</P>
<P>
   The Series dates this year for the National League teams are
Oct. 20, 21 and 22.
</P>
<P>
   All box seats for the league championship, which were $50 last
year, are now $60, while upper-deck reserve, which were $35 last
year, are $45.
</P>
<P>
   Tickets for the division series are $30 for dugout/suites, $25
for club, $20 for field and terrace, $15 for field and terrace
pavilion and $10 for upper reserved.
</P>
<P>
   ``Any time there is an increase in prices, be it regular season
and post, we hear from some fans,'' Braves senior vice president
Bob Wolfe said.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
