<DOCNO> NYT19980810.0383 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-10 20:57 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A7018 &Cx1f; ttd-z
r l &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-LEAH-PERSONALS-SFCHRO     08-10 0733
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LEAH-PERSONALS-SFCHRON </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
AND THE CHEESIEST WINNERS ARE
</HEADLINE>
  
 (Eds: This story also moved in the ``a'' national news file)  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 c.1998 San Francisco Chronicle
<TEXT>
<P>
   Film magazine's list of the five cheesiest movie lines of all
time, as interpreted in prose fit for a family newspaper:
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Demi Moore &LR;  in ``G.I. Jane'' saying, ``(Sip through a straw)
my (Nixon's first name).''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; _ Arnold Schwarzenegger &LR;  in ``The Last Action Hero''
threatening a rival, ``You want to be a farmer? Here's a couple of
ache-ers.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; _ Leonardo DiCaprio  &LR; in ``Titanic'' proclaiming, ``I'm the king
of the world.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; _ Charlie Sheen &LR;  in ``Terminal Velocity'' boasting, ``I'm much
more than a walking (male genital). I'm a flying (male genital)!''
</P>
<P>
   And  &UR; Sean Connery &LR;  in ``Just Cause'' reasoning, ``If that's a
confession, my (donkey) is a banjo!''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; JOB DESCRIPTIONS &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _ Disgraced Clinton friend  &UR; Webster Hubbell &LR;  reveals in his
memoir, ``Friends in High Places: Our Journey From Little Rock to
Washington, D.C.,'' that after Clinton was elected president, he
casually asked Hubbell if he would be coming to Washington.
</P>
<P>
   When Hubbell said yes, reports the New York Review of Books,
Clinton suggested that he work in the Justice Department. The
president said there were two questions Hubbell might pursue: who
killed JFK, and whether UFOs are real.
</P>
<P>
   ``He was dead serious,'' writes Hubbell.
</P>
<P>
   _ Speaker of the House  &UR; Newt Gingrich &LR;  has turned down an offer
from  &UR; Aaron Spelling &LR; , creator of ``Love Boat: The Next Wave,'' to
guest star in an episode. An invitation dated August 3 said that
having Gingrich on the show ``would be outstanding.''
</P>
<P>
   A Gingrich spokesman told Roll Call that the speaker had no
interest in the offer. The Washington newspaper also quoted ``one
GOP leadership aide'' (a description that sounds like the Gingrich
spokesman in sheep's clothing): ``Shouldn't that invitation have
been sent to the White House?''
</P>
<P>
   _ A sign flashing on BART TV announces that ``The IRS in Oakland
is looking for permanent part-time seasonal tax examiners,'' swell
work for intermittent curmudgeons.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; A LENNON LEGACY &LR;
</P>
<P>
   A  &UR; John Lennon &LR;  record album, ``Double Fantasy,'' that Lennon
autographed for  &UR; Mark David Chapman &LR; , the ``fan'' who killed him
five hours later, is being sold for $1.8 million.
</P>
<P>
   The album is in the possession of autograph dealer  &UR; Gary &LR; 
 &UR; Zimet &LR; , who told the New York Post that he can prove its
provenance. ``There's no question of its authenticity,'' he said.
``It has the marks where fingerprints were lifted, it's signed by
detectives and stamped with case numbers.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; PET ISSUES &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _ The happening new pet, says Teen People magazine, is the
Australian Sugar Glider, which is a pocket-size kangaroo-style
marsupial only six inches long. Further research indicates that
it's illegal to bring these animals into California.
</P>
<P>
   Herpeton Exotic Pets of Austin, Texas, which sells Gliders,
seems huffy about the ban. ``On biting, of course, any animal with
a mouth CAN bite. ... However, they hardly ever break the skin.''
</P>
<P>
   _ ``Boredom is the No. 1 cause of canine separation anxiety,''
says Dog Fancy magazine, which means that if Rover is chewing up
the sofa, it's because he hasn't got anything better to do.
</P>
<P>
   The holistic approach to curing this problem specifies adding
``variety to your dog's daily life. Explore a new route during your
evening walk. ... Leave a surprise package for your dog when you go
to work.'' At the same time, ``Start by eliminating as many sources
of stress for your dog as you can. Dogs are comforted by
predictability and schedules, so keep your daily routine on an even
keel and minimize changes.''
</P>
<P>
   Got that straight?
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; CATERING TO THE TOM CLANCY READER &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Last week's publication of the  &UR; Tom Clancy &LR;  novel ``Rainbow
Six'' will be followed in a few weeks with a computer game based on
the book. The game, the first to be inspired by a hardcover Clancy
book, is the product of Red Storm Entertainment, a company founded
by the best-selling author.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Tom Clancy reader tends to be a little older,'' Red Storm
marketing man  &UR; Dick Wnuk &LR;  told Advertising Age. ``We feel we can
introduce Tom Clancy to a younger reader through this game and
really build his readership for the future.''
</P>
<P>
   The game will utilize real footage of a SWAT team in action.
</P>
