<P>
   The focus of the story budgeted as GLF-PGA has changed. Here is
a new budget line for that story:
</P>
<P>
   REDMOND, Wash. _ Significant contrasts are part of the
adaptation process for Stephen Keppler, head professional at a
metro Atlanta club, at the 80th PGA Championship this week. On
Sunday, Keppler, 37, the four-time Georgia PGA player of the year,
longed for a few pre-flight glimpses of Sahalee Country Club, but
had no time to watch the PGA preview show on CBS-TV Sunday. It
conflicted with a member-guest tournament, a summer highlight for
Stephen and his staff. So much for research opportunities. Armed
with a few details from the weekly golf periodicals, Keppler was on
site at the tree-lined venue Monday, striking balls on the Sahalee
practice range between Colin Montgomerie and Davis Love III.
(Sheeley, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
